metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'the dopamine studio', 'description': 'Step into the Dopamine Studio and immerse yourself in professionally guided classes, or simply unwind and rejuvenate in our invigorating Barrel Sauna and Ice Bath facility during one of our guided recovery sessions. name: THREE BOONS YOGA Mitte f.k.a. Jivamukti Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'THREE BOONS YOGA Mitte f.k.a. Jivamukti Berlin', 'description': 'Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. After all, liberation is what the way of the Jivanmukta is all about.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10119', 'streetAddress': 'Brunnenstra√üe 29'}, 'telephone': '+49 30 48491948', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5344766', 'longitude': '13.3986109'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/venues%2Foriginal_2000x1125_Bild1_1616513376968717_admin.png?generation=1751976116654062&alt=media'}
description: Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. After all, liberation is what the way of the Jivanmukta is all about.

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Urban Gladiators', 'description': 'Our concept: functional training, fun and high quality support We only combine natural and functional movements. name: Rocycle Berlin Mitte
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Rocycle Berlin Mitte', 'description': 'Rocycle is an effective, sweaty and fun workout that takes your mind off everything. We make our community fit and happy. Every day. Every ride. Our full-body 45- & 60-minute workouts on a bike are uplifting experiences. Set to candlelight and fueled by epic beats, our classes are made to give you that natural high. Ride the energy of the pack as you pedal out of the saddle for most of the class, training your core and raising your heart rate. You will train your upper body with hand weights and handlebar push-ups, then finish with head-to-toe stretching. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke', 'description': 'CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke bietet auf √ºber 700 m2 CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è, Hyrox, Gewichtheben, funktionelles Fitness- und Athletiktraining sowie Physiotherapie und Physiotraining vom Feinsten. Wie erfolgt die Anmeldung f√ºr Kurse bei ICKE Die Anmeldung f√ºr die Kurse erfolgt √ºber unser Online Sales Portal: https://www.crossfiticke.com/usc/. Bei deiner Anmeldung musst du deinen vollen Namen sowie deine USC Membership Nummer angeben (USC 123456 Michael Mustermann) Vor Ort musst dann wie bei jedem USC Angebot den QR-Code scannen. 2.Welche Kurse kann ich mit meiner USC Membership besuchen? Alle Kurse die besuchen kannst, werden dir als Drop-In Optionen im Sales Portal von Icke angezeigt. 3.Wie oft kann ich mit meiner USC Membership bei CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke trainieren? Die L-Membership erlaubt es dir 4x im Monat ein CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Angebot zu nutzen. Mit der XL-Membership kannst du bis 8x im Monat CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è machen. 4.Ich habe mich f√ºr einen Kurs angemeldet, kann diesen Termin aber leider nicht wahrnehmen. Kein Problem. Ruf uns an oder schick uns eine Email und wir canceln deine Reservierung. Ber√ºcksichtige aber bitte, dass wir eine 24 Stundenfrist f√ºr Absagen haben. Solltest du deinen Termin innerhalb von 24 Stunden vor Kursbeginn absagen, gilt dies als Late-Cancelation und wir m√ºssen diesen trotzdem buchen. Nat√ºrlich buchen wir den Kurs auch, wenn du trotz Anmeldung nicht zum Training erschienen bist. 5.Wo finde ich CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke? Am einfachsten suchst du bei Google Maps nach CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Spirit Yoga - Charlottenburg', 'description': 'Mit Spirit Yoga haben wir die zwei Berliner Studios als Partner, die zu den sch√∂nsten der Stadt z√§hlen. name: Yoga Futura Neuk√∂lln
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Yoga Futura Neuk√∂lln', 'description': 'At Yoga Futura we are here to support you in establishing or deepening your yoga practice, no matter your circumstances. We believe that a steady and continuous yoga practice can benefit all, and our commitment is finding the approach that fits your individual needs. Founded by two friends, mothers and partners, this space is the manifestation of our love for yoga and community. Aside finding joy in practicing, we believe one of the greatest benefits of yoga is the connection it brings within its practitioners. Having met through yoga, our friendship symbolises the power of this union. When thinking about how we want to ensure that everyone feels welcome and safe to practice in our studio, we identified a few important principles which we have carried over into our teachings. These include placing emphasis on consent as the basis of any physical touch, ensuring that the practice is non-injurious, and fostering an environment where yoga is not synonymous with being able-bodied. The yoga that we practice and teach is not new, it is a result of the evolution that has been occurring within and outside of the yoga tradition for hundreds of years. Our approach however is unique in that it aims to re-evaluate which of these traditions still serves us today. Yoga Futura stands for a sustainable practice that will support you in all the different phases of your life.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '12059', 'streetAddress': 'Weigandufer 18'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4831013', 'longitude': '13.4471193'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2048x1152_dc2082d53fe4-ADDB06D3_6989_439A_B963_623DAE743A42_1644852605813520_admin.jpg?generation=1644852605910606&alt=media'}
description: At Yoga Futura we are here to support you in establishing or deepening your yoga practice, no matter your circumstances. We believe that a steady and continuous yoga practice can benefit all, and our commitment is finding the approach that fits your individual needs. Founded by two friends, mothers and partners, this space is the manifestation of our love for yoga and community. Aside finding joy in practicing, we believe one of the greatest benefits of yoga is the connection it brings within its practitioners. Having met through yoga, our friendship symbolises the power of this union. When thinking about how we want to ensure that everyone feels welcome and safe to practice in our studio, we identified a few important principles which we have carried over into our teachings. These include placing emphasis on consent as the basis of any physical touch, ensuring that the practice is non-injurious, and fostering an environment where yoga is not synonymous with being able-bodied. The yoga that we practice and teach is not new, it is a result of the evolution that has been occurring within and outside of the yoga tradition for hundreds of years. Our approach however is unique in that it aims to re-evaluate which of these traditions still serves us today. Yoga Futura stands for a sustainable practice that will support you in all the different phases of your life.

name: Triathlon Crew Berlin HQ
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Triathlon Crew Berlin HQ', 'description': 'Willkommen bei der Triathloncrew Berlin. Der Triathlonsport wird immer mehr zum Volkssport, bietet er doch viele M√∂glichkeiten sich sportlich zu fordern und weiterzuentwickeln. Aber aus welchen Disziplinen besteht der Triathlon? Im TRIATHLON steht als erste Disziplin das SCHWIMMEN an, gefolgt vom RADFAHREN und dem LAUFEN zum Schluss. Drei Disziplinen deren k√∂rperliche Anforderungen sehr verschieden ausfallen k√∂nnen. Entsprechend gibt es unter den Sportlern kaum jemanden der Experte in allen drei Disziplinen ist. Dieses Problem wollen wir von der Triathloncrew Berlin l√∂sen. Mitten in Berlin, Indoor und Outdoor, bieten wir ein sehr technikorientiertes Training aller Disziplinen an. Denn Schwimmen ist nicht gleich Schwimmen und Laufen nicht gleich Laufen. Die meisten unserer Kurse enthalten deshalb viele technische Komponente zur Steigerung der √ñkonomie und Effizienz, mit dem Ziel der Leistungsoptimierung. Dabei achten wir darauf immer auf dem neuesten Stand der wissenschaftlichen Lehrmeinung und Technik zu sein. Neuerungen flie√üen dabei sehr schnell in das Training mit ein. Besonders stolz sind wir darauf Berlins erstes und einziges SMART Rollentrainer-Radtraining anbieten zu k√∂nnen. Mithilfe Ihres eigenen Rades, und Ihrer eigenen individuellen Radeinstellung (auch nach Bikefitting), holen wir das Maximum aus Ihner Leistungsf√§higkeit heraus. Wir bieten folgende Kurse an: Schwimmen: ‚Ä¢tKraultechnik ‚Ä¢tKraulworkout HIT ‚Ä¢tKraultechnik Open Water ‚Ä¢tKraulworkout HIT Open Water ‚Ä¢tBike-Swim-Bike Koppeltraining Open Water Radfahren mit dem eigenen Rad (Shimano Schaltung): ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining Technik ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining VO2max ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining LIT ‚Ä¢tBike-Swim-Bike Koppeltraining ‚Ä¢tLIT Long Bike Ausfahrt Laufen: ‚Ä¢tLauftechnik und -√∂konomietraining ‚Ä¢tHIT & Run ‚Ä¢tTriathloncrew Koppeltraining ‚Ä¢tLIT Long Run Funktionelles Krafttraining: ‚Ä¢tTraining der Triathlonspezifischen Arbeitsmuskulatur ‚Ä¢tCoretraining ‚Ä¢tZugseiltraining Bei den Kursen handelt es sich um ausgesuchte Kurse, die jeweils nach Saison und Trainingsphase in das Training integriert werden k√∂nnen. Neben den Inhalten des Trainings ist eines der wichtigsten Erfolgsfaktoren zur Verbesserung der Leistungsf√§higkeit, die Kontinuit√§t des Trainings. Mit fachlicher Kompetenz, Spa√ü und Enthusiasmus freuen wir uns, Ihnen dabei unter die Arme greifen zu d√ºrfen. English: Welcome to the Triathlon Crew Berlin. Triathlon is becoming an ever more popular sport, since it offers many opportunities to challenge and further develop yourself and your sporting ability. But what disciplines does the triathlon consist of? TRIATHLON consists of SWIMMING, followed by BIKING and RUNNING at the end. Three disciplines whose physical requirements can be very different. Accordingly, there are very few athletes who are expert in all three elements. At the Triathloncrew Berlin, we love to face these challenges and build a supportive training community. Based in the middle of Berlin, with indoor and outdoor facilities, we offer very technology-oriented training in all disciplines. We recognize that swimming, cycling and running performance are built from strength, endurance and technical proficiency. Therefore, most of our courses contain many technical components to increase economy and efficiency, with the aim of optimizing performance. We make sure that we are always up to date with the latest scientific opinions and technology, enabling new innovations to flow quickly into the training. We are particularly proud to be able to offer Berlin's first and only SMART bike training. With the help of your own bike and your own individual bike setting (even after bike fitting), we get the most out of your performance. You may choose to participate in the specific training sessions that suit your needs, enabling tailored support integrated into your existing training program. In addition to the content of the training, one of the most important success factors for improving performance is the continuity of the training. With professional competence, fun and enthusiasm, we look forward to helping you.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10119', 'streetAddress': 'Gipsstra√üe 23b'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5267708', 'longitude': '13.4016153'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/venues%2Foriginal_1024x576_d144691a80ec-201802_Boomfit_403_163696888978098_admin.jpg?generation=1751977536578580&alt=media'}

Drei Disziplinen deren k√∂rperliche Anforderungen sehr verschieden ausfallen k√∂nnen. Entsprechend gibt es unter den Sportlern kaum jemanden der Experte in allen drei Disziplinen ist. Dieses Problem wollen wir von der Triathloncrew Berlin l√∂sen. Mitten in Berlin, Indoor und Outdoor, bieten wir ein sehr technikorientiertes Training aller Disziplinen an. Denn Schwimmen ist nicht gleich Schwimmen und Laufen nicht gleich Laufen. Die meisten unserer Kurse enthalten deshalb viele technische Komponente zur Steigerung der √ñkonomie und Effizienz, mit dem Ziel der Leistungsoptimierung. Dabei achten wir darauf immer auf dem neuesten Stand der wissenschaftlichen Lehrmeinung und Technik zu sein. Neuerungen flie√üen dabei sehr schnell in das Training mit ein. Besonders stolz sind wir darauf Berlins erstes und einziges SMART Rollentrainer-Radtraining anbieten zu k√∂nnen. Mithilfe Ihres eigenen Rades, und Ihrer eigenen individuellen Radeinstellung (auch nach Bikefitting), holen wir das Maximum aus Ihner Leistungsf√§higkeit heraus. Wir bieten folgende Kurse an: Schwimmen: ‚Ä¢tKraultechnik ‚Ä¢tKraulworkout HIT ‚Ä¢tKraultechnik Open Water ‚Ä¢tKraulworkout HIT Open Water ‚Ä¢tBike-Swim-Bike Koppeltraining Open Water Radfahren mit dem eigenen Rad (Shimano Schaltung): ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining Technik ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining VO2max ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining LIT ‚Ä¢tBike-Swim-Bike Koppeltraining ‚Ä¢tLIT Long Bike Ausfahrt Laufen: ‚Ä¢tLauftechnik und -√∂konomietraining ‚Ä¢tHIT & Run ‚Ä¢tTriathloncrew Koppeltraining ‚Ä¢tLIT Long Run Funktionelles Krafttraining: ‚Ä¢tTraining der Triathlonspezifischen Arbeitsmuskulatur ‚Ä¢tCoretraining ‚Ä¢tZugseiltraining Bei den Kursen handelt es sich um ausgesuchte Kurse, die jeweils nach Saison und Trainingsphase in das Training integriert werden k√∂nnen. Neben den Inhalten des Trainings ist eines der wichtigsten Erfolgsfaktoren zur Verbesserung der Leistungsf√§higkeit, die Kontinuit√§t des Trainings. Mit fachlicher Kompetenz, Spa√ü und Enthusiasmus freuen wir uns, Ihnen dabei unter die Arme greifen zu d√ºrfen. English: Welcome to the Triathlon Crew Berlin. Triathlon is becoming an ever more popular sport, since it offers many opportunities to challenge and further develop yourself and your sporting ability. But what disciplines does the triathlon consist of? TRIATHLON consists of SWIMMING, followed by BIKING and RUNNING at the end. Three disciplines whose physical requirements can be very different. Accordingly, there are very few athletes who are expert in all three elements. At the Triathloncrew Berlin, we love to face these challenges and build a supportive training community. Based in the middle of Berlin, with indoor and outdoor facilities, we offer very technology-oriented training in all disciplines. We recognize that swimming, cycling and running performance are built from strength, endurance and technical proficiency. Therefore, most of our courses contain many technical components to increase economy and efficiency, with the aim of optimizing performance. We make sure that we are always up to date with the latest scientific opinions and technology, enabling new innovations to flow quickly into the training. We are particularly proud to be able to offer Berlin's first and only SMART bike training. With the help of your own bike and your own individual bike setting (even after bike fitting), we get the most out of your performance. You may choose to participate in the specific training sessions that suit your needs, enabling tailored support integrated into your existing training program. In addition to the content of the training, one of the most important success factors for improving performance is the continuity of the training. With professional competence, fun and enthusiasm, we look forward to helping you.

name: THREE BOONS YOGA Charlottenburg f.k.a. Jivamukti B
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'THREE BOONS YOGA Charlottenburg f.k.a. Jivamukti B', 'description': 'Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. description: Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. After all, liberation is what the way of the Jivanmukta is all about.

name: Bewegungskollektiv Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Bewegungskollektiv Berlin', 'description': 'Im Bewegungskollektiv Berlin haben sich Trainer:innen und Bewegungsk√ºnstler:innen aus verschiedenen Disziplinen zusammengetan. Gemeinsam entwickeln sie eine Bewegungspraxis mit verschiedensten Einfl√ºssen, beispielsweise aus Tanz, Parkour, Martial Arts, Zirkus, Yoga und Calisthenics. Unsere Kurse vermitteln dir vielseitige Perspektiven auf Bewegung und deinen K√∂rper und erm√∂glichen so immer wieder neue Blickwinkel auf dein Training. In jeder neuen Bewegung kannst du etwas Vertrautes suchen & in bereits bekannten Bewegungsmustern kannst du aus einer anderen Perspektive etwas Neues finden. In unserem Gruppentraining erwarten dich je nach aktuellem Thema neben spielerischen Partner√ºbungen auch kraftvolle Power-Workouts oder meditative Dehnungs√ºbungen. EN: The Bewegungskollektiv Berlin is a movement collective of trainers and movement artists from different disciplines. Our movement practice is influenced by dance, parkour, martial arts, circus, yoga and calisthenics. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Haus Lebenskunst', 'description': 'Osho Dynamische Meditation - Unser Energie-Booster zum Loslassen von Blockaden und zur R√ºckverbindung mit unserer Essenz! Phase (10 Min): Wildes, unregelm√§√üiges Atmen Lass deinem Atem freien Lauf und sei dabei so wild und unregelm√§√üig wie m√∂glich. Konzentriere dich dabei ausschlie√ülich auf das Ausatmen, denn das Einatmen wird von deinem K√∂rper von alleine gesteuert. Atme so schnell und kraftvoll, wie du nur kannst ‚Äì und dann noch ein bisschen energischer. Stelle dir vor, du verwandelst dich in puren Atem. Nutze die nat√ºrlichen Bewegungen deines K√∂rpers, um noch mehr Energie zu sp√ºren. Du wirst f√ºhlen, wie diese Energie zunimmt, aber lass sie noch nicht v√∂llig in der ersten Phase entweichen. Sie ist wie ein wildes Pferd, das du behutsam z√§hmen und lenken kannst. Phase (10 Min): Sich ausdr√ºcken Jetzt ist es an der Zeit, vollkommen auszubrechen! Lass alles los, was in dir brodelt und nach Freiheit schreit. Schreie, br√ºlle, weine, h√ºpfe, sch√ºttele dich, tanze, singe, lache und tobe herum. Keine Zur√ºckhaltung, kein Halten von Emotionen! Es ist v√∂llig in Ordnung, am Anfang ein bisschen zu √ºbertreiben, um in den Fluss zu kommen. Lass deinen Verstand nicht dazwischenfunken. Sei voll und ganz im Moment, lass dein Herz die F√ºhrung √ºbernehmen. Sei absolut authentisch und hingebungsvoll dabei. Das ist deine Zeit, deine Emotionen und deine Energie zu entfesseln. Erlaube dir selbst, frei zu sein und in dieser Phase alles auszuleben, was in dir steckt. Phase (10 Min): Mit erhobenen Armen springen Jetzt wird es noch intensiver! Stehe auf und hebe deine Arme in die H√∂he. Beginne, auf und ab zu springen, und rufe dabei das Mantra "Huh! Huh! Huh!" aus deinem Bauch heraus, so tief und kraftvoll wie du nur kannst. Lasse die Vibrationen dieses Mantras durch deinen K√∂rper pulsieren. Deine Arme sollen den Himmel ber√ºhren, und deine Stimme soll die Energie nach au√üen tragen. Du bist in einem Moment v√∂lliger Ekstase und Befreiung. Kein Grund zur Zur√ºckhaltung ‚Äì lasse dich vollst√§ndig von diesem Prozess erfassen und genie√üe die Freiheit, die er dir schenkt. Deine Energie ist grenzenlos, also lass sie str√∂men! Phase (15 Min): Still sein, nichts tun Stopp! Halte abrupt inne und bleibe genau in der Position, in der du gerade bist. Versuche nicht, es dir bequem zu machen, und vermeide jede Bewegung. Jede noch so kleine Bewegung oder Ablenkung k√∂nnte die aufgebaute Energie zerstreuen, und all deine Bem√ºhungen w√§ren umsonst. Nun geht es darum, alles, was in dir geschieht, aufmerksam zu beobachten. Deine Empfindungen, Emotionen, Gedanken - lass sie einfach kommen und gehen, ohne in sie zu vertiefen oder Widerstand zu leisten. Du bist ein stiller Beobachter deines eigenen Inneren. Diese Phase erlaubt dir, in eine tiefere Ebene deines Bewusstseins einzutauchen und die Effekte der vorherigen Phasen zu verarbeiten. Bleibe ruhig und gelassen und lass die Erfahrungen auf dich wirken. Phase (15 Min): (Sich) Feiern Jetzt ist der Moment gekommen, sich von der Musik leiten zu lassen. Tanze frei und ungezwungen, dr√ºcke deinen Dank an die Sch√∂pfung aus und lass dieses Gl√ºcksgef√ºhl durch deinen gesamten K√∂rper str√∂men. Bewege dich im Rhythmus der Musik, als ob du eins mit ihr w√§rst. Dein Tanz ist eine Feier des Lebens und deiner eigenen Existenz. Du kannst die Freude und Dankbarkeit, die in dir aufsteigt, durch deinen Tanz ausdr√ºcken und sie in dein Leben mitnehmen. Lass dich von dieser Erfahrung inspirieren, und trage dieses Gef√ºhl der Freude und Dankbarkeit in deinem Herzen, wenn du aus der Meditation herauskommst. Es ist ein Geschenk, das du dir selbst gemacht hast, um dich mit deiner inneren Energie und Lebensfreude zu verbinden. Osho Dynamic Meditation‚Ñ¢ - This is our ultimate energy booster letting go blockages and re-connecting with our essence! A 5 phase process that takes you through charging, catharsis, grounding and meditation to joy and celebration. Stage 1 (10 min): Breathing Chaotically Let your breath run free and be as wild and irregular as possible. Concentrate exclusively on the exhale, because the inhale is controlled by your body on its own. Breathe as fast and as powerfully as you can - and then a little more energetically. Imagine yourself transforming into pure breath. Use your body's natural movements to feel even more energy. You will feel this energy increasing, but don't let it completely escape in the first phase yet. It is like a wild horse that you can gently tame and direct. Stage 2 (10 min): Explode Now is the time to break free completely! Let go of everything that is bubbling inside you and screaming for freedom. Scream, shout, cry, jump, shake yourself, dance, sing, laugh and romp around. No holding back, no holding emotions! It's perfectly okay to go a little overboard in the beginning to get into the flow. Don't let your mind get in the way. Be fully in the moment, let your heart take the lead. Be absolutely authentic and devoted to it. This is your time to unleash your emotions and your energy. Allow yourself to be free and live out everything that is inside of you in this phase. Phase 3 (10 min): Jump with arms raised high above Now it gets even more intense! Stand up and raise your arms in the air. Start jumping up and down while chanting the mantra "Huh! Huh! Huh!" from your belly, as deeply and powerfully as you can. Let the vibrations of this mantra pulse through your body. Let your arms touch the sky, and let your voice carry the energy outward. You are in a moment of complete ecstasy and liberation. There is no need to hold back - let this process take you completely and enjoy the freedom it gives you. Your energy is limitless, so let it flow! Phase 4 (15 min): Stop! Freeze Stop abruptly and stay exactly in the position you are in. Do not try to get comfortable and avoid any movement. Any movement or distraction, no matter how small, could dissipate the built-up energy, and all your efforts would be in vain. Now it is a matter of attentively observing everything that happens inside you. Your sensations, emotions, thoughts - just let them come and go without delving into them or resisting. You are a silent observer of your own inner self. This phase allows you to dive into a deeper level of your consciousness and process the effects of the previous phases. Remain calm and serene and let the experiences take effect on you. Phase 5 (15 min): Celebrate Now is the moment to let the music guide you. Dance freely, express your gratitude to creation and let this feeling of happiness flow through your entire body. Move to the rhythm of the music as if you are one with it. Your dance is a celebration of life and your own existence. You can express the joy and gratitude that rises within you through your dance and take it into your life. Be inspired by this experience, and carry this feeling of joy and gratitude in your heart when you come out of meditation. It is a gift you have given yourself to connect with your inner energy and joy of life.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10961', 'streetAddress': 'Mehringdamm 34'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4937291', 'longitude': '13.3876539'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_8889x5000_04d485e6bd43-Eventbild_Osho_Dynamische_Meditation1152x576px_de%20(1)_169781322876146_admin.jpg?generation=1697813228186809&alt=media'}

name: Feldenkrais Hannes Buder
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Feldenkrais Hannes Buder', 'description': 'The Feldenkrais Method is a somatic educational system, developed by Dr. Moshe Feldenkrais (1904-1984). The physicist Mosh√© Feldenkrais studied the connections of movement, awareness, thinking and feeling. As a result he developed the Feldenkrais Method, a powerful tool not only to improve human movement but also to improve the skills of the human brain. A Feldenkrais lesson guides you through a series of movement variations. It creates a space of learning and re-learning to move without stress or anxiety, to let go tensed up muscles, to improve the flexibility and availability of the body. The method is commonly used to regain full mobility after injuries and to reduce pain. It is also quite popular amongst musicians, dancers, sportsmen and other movement-related groups who need to rely on a highly differentiatet quality of movement. Basically it can be said that anyone can profit from the method since it helps to regain and keep physical and mental mobility up until old age. Hannes Buder is guiding Feldenkrais groups in a wonderful place called Fincan in Berlin Neuk√∂lln. The groups takes place every tuesday evening at 20:30 and every friday morning at 10:30 and is most commonly held in english. Please arrive a few minutes in advance. http://feldenkrais-berlin-neukoelln.de/ Die Feldenkrais-Methode ist eine nach ihrem Gr√ºnder Moshe Feldenkrais benannte Lernmethode. Moshe Feldenkrais studierte die Zusammenh√§nge zwischen Bewegung, Wahrnehmung, Denken und F√ºhlen. Angeregt von der enormen Lernf√§higkeit kleiner Kinder zeigte er einen Weg auf, wie dieses Entwicklungspotential in allen Lebensphasen bewusst genutzt werden kann. Die Feldenkrais-Lektionen sind klar strukturiert und spielerisch zugleich. Aus kleinen Bewegungen setzt sich am Ende der Stunde ein ganzer Bewegungsablauf zusammen. Im Vordergrund steht nicht das √úben auf ein vorgegebenes Ziel hin, sondern die Art und Weise wie wir etwas tun. Die Feldenkrais-Stunde f√ºhrt Sie durch eine Folge von Bewegungen, die Ihnen helfen sich freier zu bewegen und allt√§gliche Belastungen leichter zu meistern. Sie erfahren sp√ºrbar mehr Freiheit in K√∂rperhaltung, Atmung und Bewegung! Hannes Buder's Feldenkrais Gruppen finden dienstags um 20:30 und freitags um 10:30 im Fincan in Berlin Neuk√∂lln statt. Bitte kommen Sie ein paar Minuten vor Beginn. Die Gruppe wird in der Regel auf Englisch angeleitet. http://feldenkrais-berlin-neukoelln.de/ Der israelische Physiker Dr. Mosh√© Feldenkrais studierte die Zusammenh√§nge zwischen Bewegung, Wahrnehmung, Denken und F√ºhlen. Aus seinen Erkenntnissen entwickelte er eine Methode, die auf der nat√ºrlichen Lernf√§higkeit des menschlichen Nervensystems basiert. Indem Selbstwahrnehmung, K√∂rpergef√ºhl und Bewegungsempfindung geschult werden, lernen Sie Ihre Gewohnheiten wahrzunehmen und zu ver√§ndern. In der Feldenkrais-Arbeit lernt man, ung√ºnstige Bewegungs- und Haltungsmuster wahrzunehmen und zu ver√§ndern. Dabei steht nicht das Defizit im Vordergrund sondern das eigene Potenzial und die mitgebrachten F√§higkeiten. Die Methode eignet sich f√ºr alle Menschen, unabh√§ngig von Alter, k√∂rperlicher Konstitution oder Vorkenntnissen. Sie m√ºssen nur Neugier und Freude am Bewegen und Experimentieren mitbringen. Und ein wenig Geduld. Besonders Menschen mit einer Krankheit, einem Handicap oder im Kontext von Lebensver√§nderung machen von der Feldenkrais-Methode Gebrauch. Aber auch Schauspieler, Sportler, T√§nzer und Musiker nutzen diese k√∂rperliche Lernmethode f√ºr mehr Achtsamkeit beim Tun und Sein, um ihre jeweilige Qualit√§t zu verbessern. name: Kizomba mit Kizombaberlin.de - indoor
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Kizomba mit Kizombaberlin.de - indoor', 'description': 'I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10179', 'streetAddress': 'Inselstra√üe 9'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5122591', 'longitude': '13.4118726'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1125x633_9a5481caab7d-27F511FB_F648_415A_B725_BC8934B2D4A6_1657785499159017_admin.png?generation=1657785499222759&alt=media'}
description: I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe

name: Yoga Futura Kreuzberg
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Yoga Futura Kreuzberg', 'description': 'At Yoga Futura we are here to support you in establishing or deepening your yoga practice, no matter your circumstances. We believe that a steady and continuous yoga practice can benefit all, and our commitment is finding the approach that fits your individual needs. Founded by two friends, mothers and partners, this space is the manifestation of our love for yoga and community. Aside finding joy in practicing, we believe one of the greatest benefits of yoga is the connection it brings within its practitioners. Having met through yoga, our friendship symbolises the power of this union. When thinking about how we want to ensure that everyone feels welcome and safe to practice in our studio, we identified a few important principles which we have carried over into our teachings. These include placing emphasis on consent as the basis of any physical touch, ensuring that the practice is non-injurious, and fostering an environment where yoga is not synonymous with being able-bodied. The yoga that we practice and teach is not new, it is a result of the evolution that has been occurring within and outside of the yoga tradition for hundreds of years. Our approach however is unique in that it aims to re-evaluate which of these traditions still serves us today. Yoga Futura stands for a sustainable practice that will support you in all the different phases of your life.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10965', 'streetAddress': 'Kreuzbergstra√üe 30'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.489902434', 'longitude': '13.377527024'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_320x180_xdadfob0s4ddpehmjb8z_1717427859439676.png?generation=1717427859508934&alt=media'}

Our teachers offer a great variety of classes Online, Offline and Open Air: from energizing vinyasa flow and ecstatic dance to Hatha and Kundalini yoga, meditation, mantra singing and restorative yin yoga classes.

name: Berlin Contemporary Dance - Spreefeld
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Contemporary Dance - Spreefeld', 'description': 'Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10179', 'streetAddress': 'Wilhelmine-Gemberg-Weg 12'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5108369', 'longitude': '13.4249583'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_3928x2210_b7b31d13638a-_MG_5850_1653930153870620_admin.jpg?generation=1653930153980184&alt=media'}
description: Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.

name: Berlin Handstand School (Kreuzberg)
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Handstand School (Kreuzberg)', 'description': 'Luka is a mover that hasn't stopped moving since he left his IT chair some years ago. He is a bubble of ideas; about life, Acroyoga, and massage/bodywork. Very rarely a day passes without some kind of movement practice or community / teaching events. name: Evolve Yoga
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Evolve Yoga', 'description': 'Evolve is a Forrest Yoga and Mindfulness based studio. Forrest Yoga is a contemporary style of yoga that involves a strong physical practice that meets you where you are (All-levels), that is deeply healing for our current day challenges: weak core, fragile back and neck and shoulders, and exhausted and overwhelmed nervous system. Our classes are All-levels with specific attention to injuries and health issues. Every class also involves compassionate hands-on assists with the permission of the student. Registration is recommended as our classes are small and tend to fill up. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Ashtanga Yoga Berlin', 'description': 'Ashtanga Yoga Berlin (since 2004) is the place for eager Yoga practitioners who seek guidance and precise support in the advanced and subtle Yoga practices. The result is the exact opposite of the wide-spread (western) approach of ‚Äúteacher-imitation‚Äù, which directs your awareness outwards and puffs up the ego. True yogic experiences cannot arise if you look away from the self. Try the difference and you‚Äôll understand. === HOW CAN YOU LEARN MYSORE STYLE? === After a month of Mysore Style practice you will have escaped the boredom of flowery platitudes of copy-paste Yoga. But be warned: True Yoga needs method and dedication. Ashtanga is constructed to be challenging for your body, nervous system and ego structure. It‚Äôs all quite natural, just give us a call and we explain the details: +49.30.48496665. === YOU HAVE AN ASHTANGA PRACTICE? name: Berlin Contemporary Dance - ADA studio
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Contemporary Dance - ADA studio', 'description': 'Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '13357', 'streetAddress': 'Badstr. 41a'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5533873', 'longitude': '13.3772948'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1879x1057_2a0811651c69-sundaysolos_photo_Andi_Weiland_112__2__16911631329392_admin.jpg?generation=1691163132078457&alt=media'}

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Yoga In Person Sarasvati', 'description': 'Breath-Centered Yoga in English in Berlin Offering well rounded Yoga classes in a safe and open minded environment with personal attention and the intention of promoting well-being and peace of mind. name: Ashtanga Yoga Zentral
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Ashtanga Yoga Zentral', 'description': 'Ashtanga Yoga is an intensive Hatha Yoga practice with a focus on strength, stamina and flexibility. The traditional system is renowned for its Vinyasa method. This method of Yoga involves synchronising the breath with movement and positions, a process producing internal heat and a purifying sweat that detoxifies muscles and organs. Ashtanga Yoga is a moving meditation, resulting in improved circulation, a light and strong body, and a calm mind. Mysore-Style (named after the south-Indian city where it originated) is the traditional method in which Ashtanga Yoga is learned and practiced. Students receive individualised instruction within a group setting. A series of positions are taught in a specified order, progressing as the student is ready. With consistent, regular practice, the student can truly reap the benefits of Ashtanga yoga, bringing about the union of body and mind, one of the ultimate goals of yoga. Classes take place in the mornings and are open to all levels of practitioner, including those completely new to yoga.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10115', 'streetAddress': 'Grosse Hamburger Str. 19A'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5244355', 'longitude': '13.3988557'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1587x893_96345786363b-IMG_6146bb_1704871595538366_admin.jpg?generation=1704871595749486&alt=media'}

name: Berlin Contemporary Dance - UHU Studio
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Contemporary Dance - UHU Studio', 'description': 'Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '12435', 'streetAddress': 'Moosdorfstra√üe 7-9'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4880248', 'longitude': '13.4605024'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_711x399_mo1eils2qvgiuv90pjvb_1742813682430665.png?generation=1742813682513612&alt=media'}
description: Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'English Yoga Julie Blumenthal', 'description': 'Julie Blumenthal is a Yogiraj (master teacher) in the ISHTA lineage, combining asana and breathwork with accessible tools like subtle body work (mantra, chakras, energy lines etc), inspiring nondualistic philosophy, and Ayurveda. ISHTA practice adapts to each yogi‚Äôs own needs and supports them to find the practice that suits them, with humor and ease. Julie teaches in a cozy, personalized environment that will support you to heat up, chill out, tune in, and learn a little more about yoga, your practice, your body, and yourself in a non-dogmatic, non-judgmental and inspiring way. She believes we do not have to become better or different to experience yoga; we just have to use the tools of body, breath and attention to reconnect to ourselves and restore the balance, inspiration and support we need to move more easily through our lives. Classes focus on a physical, philosophical or energetic theme that changes week to week. All classes offer a well-rounded asana practice and include elements of meditation and relaxation, as well as some challenges, and lots of personal attention. A teacher of teachers, she leads workshops and Level 1 and Level 2 Yoga Alliance teacher trainings in the ISHTA style in Berlin in addition to her weekly classes. She is known for her wise sequencing, her sense of humor, her ability to make anatomy and philosophy fun and accessible to her students, and her soothing chanting at the end of class. name: Berlin Running Society
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Running Society', 'description': 'What we do: Are you tired of monotonous, long runs? Feel like you're getting nowhere? Or simply bored of running alone and looking for others to motivate and push you? Then you've come to the right place. We are Munich Running Society. A strong group of passionate and performance-driven runners who train, race, chill and brunch together - all year long! What does a usual session look like? No two trainings are ever the same. Each session usually lasts around 60-90 mins and is made up of an interval running workout - short, fast sprints followed by rest periods - and a bodyweight workout. How fit do you need to be? Anyone and everyone can join - we cater to all performance levels. You don't have to be a running pro, but you do have to be willing to work hard. name: Anne Pawlak
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Anne Pawlak', 'description': 'Curious about building real strength, stamina and coordination? Trying a holistic way of moving and breathing to improve posture and body feeling? Then you are in the right place. Anne offers exactly that in her fun and effective Warm Body - Good Vibes classes and Breath Club sessions. Anne‚Äôs practise combines elements of HIIT, Animal Moves, Dance and Yoga. The Foundation for confident movement and wellbeing is effective breathing. "Most of our daily activities take us out of our body and disrupt the body and mind connection. Breathwork allows us to return to our neutral self where we can become creative, explosive, expressive and dynamic in our body and mind. And most of all joyful and content with ourselves." Feel free to bring your own mat and towel. To make the most of your training make sure to hydrate properly about an hour before the training. Anne discovered the power of breath after overtraining her body for years, which caused hormonal imbalances and over exhaustion. Through dedicated breath and meditation practise in Japan as well as syncing her workout with her hormonal cycle, she was able to return back to a grounded balance. "Many of my clients are high performers at work and at home with little time on their hands. High workloads, higher responsibilities and even higher stress levels. This means they are often sleep poorly, feel too exhausted, and have a bad conscience when they don't give it their all in workouts. I make sure to design a balanced practise that works for them so they can feel good in their body ."', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '', 'streetAddress': 'Volkspark Friedrichshain'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5280353', 'longitude': '13.4363934'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576_e4d0b13f17a7-UrbanSports2_1624976944712241_admin.jpg?alt=media'}

name: Bihter Yoga
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Bihter Yoga', 'description': 'Bihter Yoga Yoga is a life altering experience! Hello, My name is Bihter. I believe that the discovery of the body is a life long experiment. Exchanging knowledge for me is an experience of expansion, enables us to learn from each other, grow together and support each other in this path. Besides my Hatha Yoga training within the Advaita School and mindfulness; my interest in Sufism and Buddhism as life philosophies and my interest in axis syllabus and bio-mechanics as tool kits to understand the body, shape my yoga teaching. In a 75 minutes of a yoga class I offer meditation, mindfulness, breathing techniques and classic yoga poses with a contemporary understanding enriched with bio-mechanics. Besides that I offer 60 minutes beginners class which we look into basics of yoga. I do classes with maximum 7 participants, and might be that you can‚Äôt get in if you don‚Äôt let me know you‚Äôre coming in advance. Please ring Raum5 and arrive latest 5 minutes before the class starts. name: Common Humanity - Evolve Yoga Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Common Humanity - Evolve Yoga Berlin', 'description': 'Common Humanity, Berlin's English-speaking mindfulness center, was created first and foremost to bring people together. Its mission is to create a warm and inviting space that allows members to build community, live a healthier lifestyle and tap into their own wisdom regardless of religion, background or political affiliation. As the name suggests, we have much more in common than we realize. We have much to learn from each other and we are more effective together. Through mindfulness, meditation and community we can better realize our personal potential and find greater stability in an increasingly chaotic world. Mindfulness Meditation can: * reduce stress and tension * boost your immune system * give you a greater understanding of yourself and others * prevent against "burnout" * increase your creativity * and much more Are you unfamiliar with mindfulness or mindful meditation? If so, we invite you to come and sit with us for an hour. You don't need any experience; however, all levels are welcome. Our hour-long meditations include 2-3 mindful meditations centered around a theme, followed by a short group discussion. Meditations will be in English, but please do not be intimidated. There is a great deal of silence in meditation, and you will not be required to write a master's thesis (we promise). If you have never had the opportunity to meditate in a group setting, you will find it to be a different (and potentially more enriching) experience from sitting alone. Kim Douglass is the founder and facilitator of the hour-long meditation sessions. She is an American Expat that has lived in Germany since 2006. She worked for many years in the corporate world, most recently as the Marketing Communications Manager for a tech company in Berlin. After her daughter was born in 2013, she had a serious bout with post-partum depression (PPD), which caused her to look for a solution that did not involve medication. Everything she read pointed to meditation. After much research, reading, meditating and yoga practice, she left her career to pursue a future teaching mindfulness to others because her life was changed so dramatically. Kim completed her Mindfulness, Meditation, and MBSR teacher training at Mindful Academy in Spain in 2017 and is enthusiastic about teaching people a more joyful and hopeful way to live their lives with a dash of mindfulness and a lot more kindness. You can find out more about Common Humanity on their website: www.commonhumanityberlin.com', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '12159', 'streetAddress': 'Rheinstra√üe 67'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.471812', 'longitude': '13.335946'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576_MeditationEvolve_1551431177266126_admin.jpg?alt=media'}
description: Common Humanity, Berlin's English-speaking mindfulness center, was created first and foremost to bring people together. Its mission is to create a warm and inviting space that allows members to build community, live a healthier lifestyle and tap into their own wisdom regardless of religion, background or political affiliation. As the name suggests, we have much more in common than we realize. We have much to learn from each other and we are more effective together. Through mindfulness, meditation and community we can better realize our personal potential and find greater stability in an increasingly chaotic world. Mindfulness Meditation can: * reduce stress and tension * boost your immune system * give you a greater understanding of yourself and others * prevent against "burnout" * increase your creativity * and much more Are you unfamiliar with mindfulness or mindful meditation? If so, we invite you to come and sit with us for an hour. You don't need any experience; however, all levels are welcome. Our hour-long meditations include 2-3 mindful meditations centered around a theme, followed by a short group discussion. Meditations will be in English, but please do not be intimidated. There is a great deal of silence in meditation, and you will not be required to write a master's thesis (we promise). If you have never had the opportunity to meditate in a group setting, you will find it to be a different (and potentially more enriching) experience from sitting alone. Kim Douglass is the founder and facilitator of the hour-long meditation sessions. She is an American Expat that has lived in Germany since 2006. She worked for many years in the corporate world, most recently as the Marketing Communications Manager for a tech company in Berlin. After her daughter was born in 2013, she had a serious bout with post-partum depression (PPD), which caused her to look for a solution that did not involve medication. Everything she read pointed to meditation. After much research, reading, meditating and yoga practice, she left her career to pursue a future teaching mindfulness to others because her life was changed so dramatically. Kim completed her Mindfulness, Meditation, and MBSR teacher training at Mindful Academy in Spain in 2017 and is enthusiastic about teaching people a more joyful and hopeful way to live their lives with a dash of mindfulness and a lot more kindness. We can't wait to dance with you.

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Fortuna wetten - Tanzen mit Barbara Berti', 'description': 'Class of contact improvisation and movement (followed from a Jam of Contact improvisation) The class invites you to dive into some of the understanding of the language of Contact Improvisation, to deepen our awareness, stretch and transform the possibilities of the body. By practicing the dialogue of shared axes and weight moving through space, we will stimulate our natural curiosity for the unknown: We will enter a state of exploration, sinking into the intuitive responses of our bodies, observing them and using them for our dialogue with the partner. This class is open for all, beginners who wish to enter into this practice as well as experienced dancers and contacters, who wish to further develop and fine tune their skills Der Kurs l√§dt dazu ein, in das Verst√§ndnis der Sprache der Contact Improvisation einzutauchen, um unser Bewusstsein zu vertiefen, die M√∂glichkeiten des K√∂rpers zu dehnen und zu transformieren. name: Fridays only@bewegtundklar
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Fridays only@bewegtundklar', 'description': 'Thaimassage, manchmal auch Yogamassage genannt, ist eine dynamische Massage bei der ich als Massierende neben meinen H√§nden z.B. auch Unterarme, F√º√üe und Beine einsetzen kann. Die Bewegungen sind sanft und dynamisch, ich arbeite mit Druck und Zug und mobilisiere Gelenke Gelenke, B√§nder und Sehnen durch Bewegung. Auch klassische Massagetechniken f√ºr den R√ºcken und Nacken findest du bei mir. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Heilpraxis Patricia Wilhelm ', 'description': 'Heilpraxis Patricia Wilhelm ‚Äì Akupunktur, Chiropraktik, (Klang) Massage (nur f√ºr Frauen) & Yoga in Sch√∂neberg Mein Name ist Patricia Wilhelm ‚Äì sch√∂n, dass du zu mir findest. name: Hoop Plus Fit 2
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Hoop Plus Fit 2', 'description': 'Hula hooping is an excellent way to get fit, stay strong and an excellent party trick to pull in front of your friends! I alternate the focus weekly between fitness Hooping and tricks classes. The fitness focused classes begin with core strengthening exercises. We work mainly with waist hooping in order to build the strength and control needed to dance freely with the hoop around the waist and improve flow. In the tricks classes we train new skills and work on getting a better technique at every stage. I break down tricks into small achievable steps and which we use as building blocks for getting the trick. I also teach the tricks in small sequences, so we learn how to flow in and out of them from the beginning. As well as how to time your movement to the music. Aside from the Class I also run the The Hoop Plus Jam. This is is an open training session with a live DJ every week.There is a great sound system there, so you can feel the music and flow. Get Fit! Learn Tricks! name: Hyon Haeng Martial Arts
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Hyon Haeng Martial Arts', 'description': 'Sweat more in training, bleed less in battle. Following this creed this course aims to invigorate your body and mind, enable you to defend yourself and get you ready for combat. Chinese Martial Arts combines hundreds of disciplines for self defence and holistic fitness, which were developed and improved over centuries in the Middle Kingdom. They connect techniques for physical, mental and spiritual balance, which makes them useful for everybody at any stage of life. ' Aldo started his trainings at the age of 16 with Wushu and Sanda in Mexico City. After several years of intensive training he became a diciple of the Shaolin monk Shi Yan Bin to learn the wisdom and techniques of Shaolin Kung Fu. In 2004 he finally was able to go to China to receive a comprehensive training in a multitude of Chinese Martial Arts disciplines. Now he is bringing that wisdom to Berlin to share it with you. In this course the techniques of Sanda, Kickboxing, Shaolin kung fu, Tai chi and Choy lei fut are combined to not only help you reach your training goals, but also to strengthen your confidence and your resiliency. Curious? Come over and embrace the challenge', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '13355', 'streetAddress': 'Pavilion im Humboldthain, Brunnenstra√üe'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5452109', 'longitude': '13.3847715'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2048x1152_d16d4402da88-photo_output_1693232080253287_admin.jpg?generation=1693232080330955&alt=media'}
description: Sweat more in training, bleed less in battle. Following this creed this course aims to invigorate your body and mind, enable you to defend yourself and get you ready for combat. Chinese Martial Arts combines hundreds of disciplines for self defence and holistic fitness, which were developed and improved over centuries in the Middle Kingdom. They connect techniques for physical, mental and spiritual balance, which makes them useful for everybody at any stage of life. ' Aldo started his trainings at the age of 16 with Wushu and Sanda in Mexico City. After several years of intensive training he became a diciple of the Shaolin monk Shi Yan Bin to learn the wisdom and techniques of Shaolin Kung Fu. In 2004 he finally was able to go to China to receive a comprehensive training in a multitude of Chinese Martial Arts disciplines. Now he is bringing that wisdom to Berlin to share it with you. In this course the techniques of Sanda, Kickboxing, Shaolin kung fu, Tai chi and Choy lei fut are combined to not only help you reach your training goals, but also to strengthen your confidence and your resiliency. Curious? Come over and embrace the challenge

name: Inner Peace
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Inner Peace', 'description': 'Yoga means unity or connection. Therefore, the best place to practise yoga is nature. You can feel the fresh air, the grasses, the trees. It will be easier to connect ourselves to nature. That is the sole purpose of scheduling the class in a park. I am an Indian born teacher. Yoga is not just a practise but also my culture. I use the traditional and the most authentic method. During the one hour session you will surely feel the energy radiating through your body. The class will start with the "mantra chanting", the most important thing to start the class with, and of couse you will be explained the meaning and purpose behind it. Then we will start with the classical Asanas, and various technique to matser it, the we will go ahead with some breathing technique and end the class with Shava Asana, a hyper relaxed state of body.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '', 'streetAddress': 'Humboldthain park'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.546244', 'longitude': '13.386809'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1242x699_3a36e70c92fa-IMG_7673_1631521922458772_admin.jpg?generation=1631521922550260&alt=media'}

name: Integral Relaxation and Prengnancy Massage
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Integral Relaxation and Prengnancy Massage', 'description': 'Integral Relaxing Massage, also for pregnants, near to Senefelderplatz - Prenzlauer Berg I am offering fascia touch, deep release massages, done with oil and OE essentials oils used in aromatherapies. You will have a calm and spacious room to relax and receive body work, while listening to calm music. Durch das flie√üende Zusammenspiel von passiven Dehnen, compression/decompression und dynamisch rhytmischen Bewegungen aus der Thaimassage und Osteopathie entsteht ein Zustand von "meditation in movement" zwischen Geber und Nehmer. Durch den Wechsel von passiv, statisch und rhytmisch ausgef√ºhrten Bewegungen des Behandelten k√∂nnen Blockaden auf verschiedensten Ebenen durch den Energieaustausch transformiert werden. Der K√∂rper wird angeregt sich selbst wieder zu heilen, Fehlhaltungen zu korrigieren, Chronische Leiden die nach der TCM Lehre ihren mit Ursprung in den Organen haben, k√∂nnen so nach mehrmaligen Behandlungen verschwinden Die dynamische ThaiYogamMassage ist ausgerichtet auf ganzheitliche Harmonisierung des Behandelten und dient der Entspannung auf allen Ebenen. Die dynamische Form dieser Massagetechnik stammt von Ajahn Chaiyuth Pryasith einem Meister und Lehrer aus dem Norden Thailands. Mit flie√üenden, schaukelnden, oszillierenden Behandlungsformen lade ich den Behandelnden auf meditative Weise ein loszulassen und sich hin und abzugeben. TokSen ist eine Klopfmassage ebenso mit Ursprung aus dem Norden Thailands. Bei der Klopfmassage TokSen (Tok - klopf, Sen-meridian) wird die jeweilige Region mittels eines Holzkeils behandelt. Das so rhytmisch ausgef√ºhrte Klopfen l√∂st Schwingungen aus die tiefer als bei klassischen Massagen in den K√∂rper dringt. Das Ger√§usch des rhythmischen Klopfens hat zudem eine tiefenentspannende Wirkung. Die einzigartige Technik l√∂st blockierte Meridiane und allgemeine Verspannungen. Die 2600 Jahre alte Technik wirkt tiefenentspannend, die ausgel√∂ste Vibration dringt tief in die Haut, Muskeln bis in das Fasziengewebe. Die Schwingungen bewirken einen reflektorischen Effekt der R√ºckenmarksnerven und die Meridiane, leitbahnen der Lebenskraft Ki werden direkt bearbeitet. Ein energetisches Gleichgewicht im K√∂rper wird wieder hergestellt. TokSen wird in bequemer Kleidung, liegend, sitzend und auf Matten auf dem Boden ausgef√ºhrt. Die Fu√üreflexzonenmassage dient zur Entspannung und Harmonisierung des K√∂rpers. Da im Fu√übereich alle Meridiane repr√§sentiert werden, kann so called stocked energy wieder gel√∂st werden und Energie wieder nach oben gesandt werden. Mit und ohne √ñlen m√∂glich.

name: Kizomba mit Kizombaberlin.de - outdoor
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Kizomba mit Kizombaberlin.de - outdoor', 'description': 'I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10437', 'streetAddress': 'Mauerpark'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.54553', 'longitude': '13.404'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1125x633_9a5481caab7d-27F511FB_F648_415A_B725_BC8934B2D4A6_1657788682963547_admin.png?generation=1657788683022589&alt=media'}
description: I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe

name: Kostis Spyrou - Dance
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Kostis Spyrou - Dance', 'description': 'Kostis Spyrou (b. Athens, Greece, 1989) is a Berlin-based dancer and educator focussed on the human body and its potential as a means of communication and expression. Kostis trained at the KSOT and AKTINA professional contemporary dance training programs in Athens, Greece, where he studied performance, technique, pedagogy, and choreography. Subsequently, he has supplemented his movement knowledge through parkour, acrobatics, and floor-barre as well as through strength, flexibility, and conditioning training. Since 2016, he has been working in Germany as both a professional dance artist and as an instructor in university, dance school, and studio contexts. Kostis offers regular classes and workshops at multiple venues in Berlin. Intentionally focussed on specific themes and key ideas, the classes are suitable for beginner, intermediate and advanced movers and designed to challenge, motivate, and educate.
